msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:186
msgid "Tracking workflows (:guilabel:`Blur...`, :guilabel:`Highlight...`, :guilabel:`Mask...`) use a region screen where you mark what to include and what to ignore."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:193
msgid "Why this matters"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:195
msgid "Tracking helps your effect stay attached to a moving subject over time. For example, you can blur a face, highlight a player, or generate a clean mask that follows the same object across many frames."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:200
msgid "Tracking Icons"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:206
msgid "Icon / Marker"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:207
msgid "Meaning"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:208
msgid "Blue dot"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:209
msgid "Positive tracking coordinate (foreground/subject seed point)."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:210
msgid "Red dot"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:211
msgid "Negative tracking coordinate (background/exclusion seed point)."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:212
msgid "Blue rectangle"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:213
msgid "Positive region seed (broad subject hint)."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:214
msgid "Red rectangle"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:215
msgid "Negative region seed (broad exclusion hint)."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:216
msgid "Delete icon"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:217
msgid "Clear all current tracking seeds (points/rectangles) and start over."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:220
msgid "How Tracking Works"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:222
msgid "OpenShot sends your positive and negative markers as seed coordinates to the tracking model, which builds a mask for the subject and then follows it over time. Better seeds usually produce cleaner masks and less drift. [sam2]_"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:227
msgid "How to use it"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:229
msgid "Pick a frame where the subject is clearly visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:230
msgid "Start with one blue dot on the subject."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:231
msgid "Add red dots on nearby background only if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:232
msgid "Add rectangles when you need faster broad selection."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:233
msgid "Repeat on additional frames when motion/shape changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:235
msgid "Adjusting over time (frame slider):"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:237
msgid "Move the frame slider to different moments in the clip."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:238
msgid "Add or adjust dots/rectangles on frames where tracking starts to drift."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:239
msgid "Use additional seed points only where needed, especially on occlusions, fast motion, or major shape changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:241
msgid "**Mask Preview Output (from this tracking process):**"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:246
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:248
msgid "Use a short test clip first."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:249
msgid "Start simple: a single blue dot is often enough."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:250
msgid "Add more points only where tracking fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:251
msgid "If needed, add a more nuanced set of positive/negative points and rectangles."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:252
msgid "Keep positive and negative points separated clearly."
msgstr ""

#: ../ai.rst:253
msgid "If tracking becomes messy, use the Delete icon and restart with cleaner seeds."
msgstr ""

